headline: Intel Stock Surges to 4-Year High Ahead of Earnings. Why Optimism Is Growing.
summary: Intel  stock gained again on Wednesday ahead of the chip company’s earnings report.  Intel shares were up 11.7% at $54.25 for the session, their highest close since January 2022.  Intel is expected to report adjusted earnings of eight cents a share on revenue of $13.42 billion for the fourth quarter of 2025, according to a FactSet poll of analysts’ estimates.
